  "original_title": "\u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0bb1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Import restriction for one year",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Power and Energy, Kanjana Wijesekara, said today (25) that the National Fuel Permit (QR) system will be implemented at Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation and Lanka IOC fuel stations nationwide.",
        "He mentioned that the fuel supply system based on the final digit of vehicle number plate will continue till August 1st and after that only QR system will be fully implemented.",
        "He also mentioned that due to foreign exchange issues, fuel imports have to be curbed in the next 12 months.",
        "He also mentioned that even if fuel stock is unlimited, daily supply to fuel stations is practically impossible.",
        "He also mentioned that health, agriculture, fisheries, tourism, industry and service sectors will be given access to the system to register their vehicles in the permit system."
      ],
